# Feature scaffold: `src/features/<feature>/`

Use this layout for new Nest features in this repository.

```
src/features/<feature>/
  <feature>.module.ts          # Nest module wiring
  application/                 # Use cases, jobs, application services
    <feature>.service.ts
    *.cron.ts                  # optional scheduled tasks
  domain/                      # Entities & domain types
    <feature>.entity.ts
  infra/                       # External systems, provider adapters
    <feature>-provider.service.ts
  interface/                   # HTTP / WebSocket surface
    <feature>.controller.ts
    <feature>.gateway.ts       # if WebSocket
    dto/
      *.dto.ts
  MODULE_DOC.md
  *.md                         # optional deep-dives (flows, architecture)
```

# Rules

- Register the feature in `app.module.ts` (or a parent module) via `<feature>.module.ts`.
- Add the **canonical file header** (see `.cursor/rules/header.template.mdc`) to each new file.
- Use **`Logger` from `@nestjs/common`** (or project logger wrapper) in services; log important failures with context; avoid `console.log` in `src/`.
- Prefer **unit tests** (`*.spec.ts`) beside services/controllers; add **integration tests** with Testcontainers/Postgres when the feature touches the DB in non-trivial ways.
- Update **MODULE_DOC.md** (purpose, APIs, env vars, changelog) when behavior changes.
